16 Che per l’effetto de’ suo’ mai pensieri, 17 fidandomi di lui, io fossi preso 18 e poscia morto, dir non è mestieri;
19 però quel che non puoi avere inteso, 20 cioè come la morte mia fu cruda, 21 udirai, e saprai s’e’ m’ha offeso.

query.result:
**English:**
16 That because of the effect of his evil thoughts, 17 trusting in him, I was captured 18 and then killed, there is no need to say;
19 therefore what you cannot have understood, 20 that is, how cruel my death was, 21 you will hear, and you will know if he has wronged me.
**Old English:**
16 Þæt for ðæs wyrdes gewealdum, 17 me selfum to truwie, ic wæs genumen 18 and syððan ofslegen, nis ðearf ðæt secgan;
19 forðæm ðæt ðu ne miht habban ongieten, 20 ðæt is, hu min deað wæs reðe, 21 ðu gehyrst, and ðu wast gif he me hafað gedon unriht.

